raw_91_caveat=R-pentomino on infinite plane: ~1103 generations of debris before stabilizing. On 80x80 toroidal: wavefront radius ~40 cells, so first ~40 generations are boundary-free aperiodic; subsequent generations include toroidal interference. The 1515-step trajectory necessarily contains BOTH chaotic-spread AND post-collision phases.
raw_91_caveat=Order-1 Markov per-cell bigram: 4 counts per cell × 6400 cells = 25600 counts vs T8j 6400 vs T8i 400 — capacity scales linearly with grid; if H1 holds, structural advantage holds even with 4x larger Markov capacity than T8j.
raw_91_caveat=Per-cell independence assumption in Markov is the structural blind spot — order-1 cannot represent neighbor coupling, which IS the Conway rule. If H1/H3 holds on aperiodic init, Law 64 v5 restoration says: structural law conditional on (aperiodic_init), not unconditional.
raw_91_caveat=Single seed / single init position. H1 or H3 confirmation under one seed is suggestive, not conclusive — multi-init-position sweep is forward step C5_T8l.
